Subject: VBO:0017483
Value: Warmbloods are a group of middle-weight horse types and breeds primarily originating in Europe and registered with organizations that are characterized by open studbook policy, studbook selection, and the aim of breeding for equestrian sport.

Subject: VBO:0100118
Value: A cat of mixed ancestry that has not been intentionally bred and possess a coat of long fur.

Subject: VBO:0100119
Value: A cat of mixed ancestry that has not been intentionally bred and possess a coat of short fur.

Subject: VBO:0100265
Value: A cat of mixed ancestry that has not been intentionally bred and possess a coat of semi-long fur.

Subject: VBO:0300002
Value: Breed recognition status referring to a breed recognized by an international breed registration body. This status also refers to breeds that are eligible to compete in championship classes.

Subject: VBO:0300004
Value: Breed recognition status referring to a breed that is reported by an international breed registration body but not recognized.

Subject: VBO:0300009
Value: Risk of extinction is determined using matrix based on the breeding population and reproductive capacity of the breed (https://www.fao.org/dad-is). It should be noted that the extinction risk criteria might differ between the international breed organizations.

Subject: VBO:0300010
Value: Extinction status given to a group of animals in which the number of breeding males and/or females is sufficient to maintain the existence of the breed.

Subject: VBO:0300011
Value: Extinction status given to a group of animals in which the breeding population (ie number of breeding males and/or females, and/or the number of living animals belonging to a breed) is reduced to a level that is threatening the existence of the breed.
